Post: Happy #WorldHealthDay! We've been sharing workouts that you can do at home so you can keep yourself healthy and fit ‚Äî but remember that it is just as important to keep your mind in good shape. Practice mindfulness, give yourself the breaks that you deserve, give time to what you love, and do what aligns with your moral compass because these are the ways that you take care of your mental well-being. At the end of this pandemic and lockdown, make sure that you stay in agreement with yourself.

Post: Sun Life Foundation, in partnership with ECHOSI Foundation, started Project TALA (Tradition, Arts, and Livelihood Advocacy) to help preserve the inabal weaving tradition of the Bagobo-Tagabawa tribe in Bansalan, Davao del Sur through livelihood-building activities and skills training. In this initiative, the Bagobo-Tagabawa tribeswomen take the lead in planning, implementation, and management of community development initiatives, which in the past were the domain of men. #WomensMonth #BrighterWorldBuilders

Post: We are extending the grace period for premium payments to 91 days to make things a bit easier for our clients during this trying time. This extension is applicable for policies or pre-need plans with due dates falling from Feb. 15 to May 31, 2020. We will also start accepting soft copies of requirements related to any insurance claims. See our other advisories here: bit.ly/2w7FZlr #sunlifeadvisory
